12/12/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Anti-Corruption Department (DNA) on Tuesday (December 11th) launched an investigation against former Environment Minister Aurel Constantin Ilie in relation to a land concession deal. Ilie, who served in the Social Democrats cabinet from 2002 to 2004, is suspected of illegally giving a 183-acre land plot to an Austrian real estate company, despite the fact that 100 rightful owners of the plot had claims on the land. 
Separately, the DNA issued arrest warrants against two senior magistrates -- Dimitru Gheorghe and Gheorghe Bucur. The two men are part of a group of six senior magistrates suspected of rigging a contest held to assign the heads of the prosecution offices in Bucharest and Pitesti.
In other news Tuesday, prosecutors filed charges against 21 customs officers at Bucharest's Henri Coanda International Airport. They are suspected of committing 8,121 act of corruption in one year. According to prosecutors, between December 2005 and September 2006 the officers accepted bribes totalling 23,000 euros. (Nine o'clock - 12/12/07; Rompres, Mediafax - 11/12/07)
